mods:mods.mods:note: This item was digitised as part of a project in 2018 and 2019 to digitise the first 10 editions of Encyclopaedia Britannica. The collection was digitised at the National Library of Scotland’s Causewayside studio. Editions 1-5 were digitised through an external contractor, Picturae. Editions 6-10 were digitised by the National Library of Scotland. Transcriptions were generated from optical character recognition (OCR) performed by the National Library of Scotland. All fold-outs were digitised by the National Library of Scotland. The collection was digitised as part of the ‘One Third Digital’ strategic aim, and to coincide with the 250th anniversary of the publication of the first edition. The digitisation was funded through private donations received as part of a public fundraising campaign.
